{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-single-blog-js","path":"/blogs/seriously-what-s-the-web","result":{"data":{"sanityBlog":{"title":"Seriously, What's The Web?","_rawBody":[{"_key":"1b37d0ef27d5","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"53b13adef6a00","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Heres how...it was invented by Sir Tim Berners-Lee in 1989 while he was working at the European Organization for Nuclear Research (CERN) in Switzerland."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"bb6c6edb97f3","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"7b5c9af9d7930","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"At the time, CERN had many researchers from around the world who needed a way to share information and collaborate on research projects. Berners-Lee saw an opportunity to use hypertext, a technology that allowed users to access and link to different pages of information, to create a system for sharing and organizing research documents."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"6c4fe3bea175","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"664cbe5b41a30","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"In March 1989, Berners-Lee submitted a proposal to CERN for what he called the \"Mesh\" system, which would allow researchers to access and share information over the internet. His proposal included the use of three key technologies: Hypertext Markup Language (HTML) for creating web pages, Uniform Resource Locators (URLs) for identifying the location of web pages, and Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP) for transferring data between web servers and clients."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"e47e65b0550b","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"bd79e52440a90","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Over the next few years, Berners-Lee and his colleagues developed and refined these technologies, and in 1991, they made the first public announcement of the World Wide Web. The web quickly gained popularity, and by the mid-1990s, it had become a major platform for information sharing and communication around the world. Today, the web is an essential part of our daily lives, and it continues to evolve and change as new technologies and trends emerge."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"}],"coverImage":{"asset":{"gatsbyImageData":{"images":{"sources":[],"fallback":{"src":"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?w=5616&h=3744&auto=format","srcSet":"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?rect=0,2,5616,3738&w=320&h=213&auto=format 320w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?w=654&h=436&auto=format 654w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?w=768&h=512&auto=format 768w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?rect=1,0,5613,3744&w=1024&h=683&auto=format 1024w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?rect=1,0,5614,3744&w=1366&h=911&auto=format 1366w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?rect=1,0,5614,3744&w=1600&h=1067&auto=format 1600w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?w=1920&h=1280&auto=format 1920w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?rect=0,0,5616,3743&w=2048&h=1365&auto=format 2048w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?rect=1,0,5615,3744&w=2560&h=1707&auto=format 2560w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?rect=0,0,5616,3743&w=3440&h=2293&auto=format 3440w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?w=3840&h=2560&auto=format 3840w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?rect=0,0,5615,3744&w=4096&h=2731&auto=format 4096w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/production/73ca0d5e0e7f968b3859e7479e1757f8fbb9e116-5616x3744.jpg?w=5616&h=3744&auto=format 5616w","sizes":"(min-width: 5616px) 5616px, 100vw"}},"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#61371b","width":5616,"height":3744}},"alt":"image of the web"},"categories":[{"title":"Web Development","slug":{"current":"web-development"}}],"author":{"name":"John Migwi","slug":{"current":"john"}},"PublishedAt":"2023-02-16T14:20:46.160Z"}},"pageContext":{"id":"-db88b002-d06e-54c5-8472-b44f07806fc5"}},"staticQueryHashes":["196044662"]}